## Configure protected directories in Apache KodeKloud Engineer Task Success

### Question : 

1.  Create /var/www/html/dba direcotry if doesn't exist.

2.  Add a user kirsty in htpasswd and set its password to 8FmzjvFU6S.

3. There is a file /tmp/index.html placed on Jump Server. Copy the same to new directory you created, please make sure default document root should remain /var/www/html. Also website should work on URL http://<app-server-hostname>:<port>/dba

Solution:  
1. At first  copy the index file from jump server to app server

    scp /tmp/index.html banner@stapp03:/tmp

2.  Login on app server  

```
sshpass -p BigGr33n ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no banner@stapp03

sudo su -
```

3. Run Below command to check the existing Apache httpd service status 

     `systemctl status httpd`

4. Create /var/www/html/dba directory (Please refer your task)

    `mkdir /var/www/html/dba`


5. Add a user and set password as per given in your task 

    `htpasswd -c /etc/httpd/.htpasswd  kirsty`




6. create .htaccess file under dba directory ( refer Video below )

    `vi  /var/www/html/dba/.htaccess`

    Add below in configuration file 
```
    AuthType Basic

    AuthName "Password Required"

    Require valid-user

    AuthUserFile /etc/httpd/.htpasswd
```


7. Move the copied index.html file under dba directory 
    `mv /tmp/index.html  /var/www/html/dba/`



8. Post saved config file , start  & check the httpd services status

`systemctl start httpd && systemctl status httpd`





9.  Validate Apache httpd running  as per the task request user and password

 `curl -u kirsty http://stapp03:8080/dba`

